definition: to set out/to start
to go forward/to advance/to go in/to enter/to put in/to submit/to take in/to admit/(math.) base of a number system/classifier for sections in a building or residential compound
to send out/to show (one's feeling)/to issue/to develop/to make a bundle of money/classifier for gunshots (rounds)

sentences.english: Master Wang is the leader of the Hong Men, a group which is noted for its kungfu skills.
sentences.chinese: 王進發師傅是洪門的山主，該門派以其功夫技巧聞名。

sentences.english: I embarked toward the sixth beacon.
sentences.chinese: 我向着第六個烽火臺進發。

sentences.english: Now he was himself plumbing an unfathomable sea.
sentences.chinese: 現在他自已正在向那深不可測的海底進發。

sentences.english: The Russians were now heading for Berlin.
sentences.chinese: 至此，俄國人向柏林進發。

sentences.english: They were heading almost due east.
sentences.chinese: 他們幾乎是朝著正東方向進發。

sentences.english: They may be heading south. Repeat. Heading South.
sentences.chinese: 它們正朝南進發，重複一遍，朝南。

sentences.english: After an hour's rest at Luodian, we proceeded to Taicang.
sentences.chinese: 在羅店休息了一小時，我們向太倉進發。

sentences.english: Tourists climb to the top of Wuyi Mountain in Fujian, China.
sentences.chinese: 在中國福建，遊客們正在向武夷山頂進發。

sentences.english: He ordered the 20 boats linked by long ropes and set out for the north shore.
sentences.chinese: 遂命將二十隻船，用長索相連，徑望北岸進發。

sentences.english: With the young man leading, they started toward the mountain.
sentences.chinese: 由那位年輕人帶路，他們開始朝山上進發。

sentences.english: We got up to where the cliff face seemed to loom over us.
sentences.chinese: 我們朝崖面那好像朦蓋着我們的那處進發。

sentences.english: It gets you started toward desktops of the future, today.
sentences.chinese: 如今，它正引領着您向未來的桌面系統進發。

sentences.english: In July 1768, the Endeavour set out for the Pacific.
sentences.chinese: 在1768年七月，“奮進號”向太平洋進發。

sentences.english: The British army was directed from Scutari, a large village near Constantinople .
sentences.chinese: 英軍從君士坦丁堡附近的一個大村子斯庫臺開始進發。

sentences.english: Their foes, the Kuomintang, loomed in the distance, advancing on the garrison town of Yan’an.
sentences.chinese: 敵人國民黨在遠方出現，向軍事重鎮延安進發。

sentences.english: But all four members of the family were good sports, so we soldiered on to the fourth column.
sentences.chinese: 但是一家四口都有體育精神，所以我們向第四列進發。
